Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.15,0:00:08.98,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Whatever it is you want to see, \NI want to help you see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.99,0:00:12.96,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If there's something you \Ndon't know, I'll teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.96,0:00:17.13,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Though, when you want to achieve something \Nsolely through your own efforts, I won't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.57,0:00:20.98,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,What kind of scholar will you become?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.98,0:00:23.79,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm very much looking forward to finding out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.48,0:00:27.42,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Why do you take such good care of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.84,0:00:35.71,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Perhaps because this may be the only \Ngood thing I am able to do in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.89,0:00:47.04,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.73,0:00:49.31,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Hey there, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.16,0:00:54.52,Default,Lawvine's knight 2,0,0,0,,Please stand back!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.16,0:00:57.19,Default,Lawvine's knight 1,0,0,0,,This suspicious person has declared
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.19,0:00:59.91,Default,Lawvine's knight 1,0,0,0,,he will cause an act of violence \Nin town at six this evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.91,0:01:01.74,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,It's just as he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.17,0:01:06.58,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,And you think that by doing so, Prince \NArnold will hear of the power of black powder?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.64,0:01:09.84,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.84,0:01:13.28,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Such an action will affect people \Nunrelated to this matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.28,0:01:15.31,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.31,0:01:16.22,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.97,0:01:19.97,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Well, its unveiling demands as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.94,0:01:23.17,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,As it's something I have created...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.69,0:01:26.48,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I must take responsibility for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.33,0:01:31.86,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Even if it means causing \Nmisfortune for someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.51,0:01:37.91,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,My own existence is just the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.36,0:01:40.32,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.14,0:02:03.61,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,The words of a person like me... shouldn't \Nbe taken at face value.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.47,0:02:09.81,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Taking you on as my student was \Nno more than a whim of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.23,0:02:15.25,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.13,0:02:26.08,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I once asked the professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.47,0:02:31.29,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Is it truly impossible for a poison \Nto bring someone happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.46,0:02:36.55,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But instead of asking...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:42.30,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor, I may only have been \Nyour student for a brief time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.36,0:02:46.68,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,but I can say this with certainty...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:52.12,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,even a poison can bring happiness to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.60,0:02:59.74,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,My alchemy teacher once told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:05.16,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,"If one fails to take all variables into \Naccount, the experiment will fail."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.83,0:03:10.41,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,No matter how great an \Nalchemist you may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.41,0:03:13.66,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,your results will not always \Nbe as you anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.18,0:03:16.21,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,That is because...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.21,0:03:21.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,it was impossible for you to \Ncomprehend the variable that I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:22.94,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.02,0:03:35.93,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.19,0:03:41.99,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor, the things you \Ncreate aren't only poisons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.42,0:03:47.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even if you can only think of them as \Nthings which bring misfortune to others,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.09,0:03:50.87,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,if their method of use is changed, \Nmany other types of value appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.64,0:04:12.56,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Colored flames?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.00,0:04:16.18,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,The black powder exploded in the sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.30,0:04:18.74,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,What is all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.21,0:04:25.66,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I once looked for a simple way to \Ndifferentiate between types of metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.36,0:04:31.95,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,At that time, someone showed me the \Nbeautiful aurora, and I remembered...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.48,0:04:36.68,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,When fire is applied to metal, \Nit gives off a beautiful light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:39.82,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.82,0:04:43.77,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,When metals are burned, the \Nflames turn different colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.77,0:04:44.54,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.04,0:04:47.81,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,However, that wasn't all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:50.27,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,With a new perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.27,0:04:53.89,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I obtained a method to \Nchange the colors of a flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.31,0:04:57.97,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Tiny lights, floating in the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.97,0:05:02.55,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,they may look like the torches of \Nwar, or like the lights of fireflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.55,0:05:07.32,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Each and every material and phenomenon \Nholds more than one meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.65,0:05:10.33,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,So does the black powder, and \Nso do you, Professor Michel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:15.33,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,There is nothing which exists solely \Nto bring misfortune to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:20.63,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,And you plotted all of this \Nto make me understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.46,0:05:23.21,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Why would you go so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:26.72,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Because I am your student.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.12,0:05:31.65,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If you wish to repudiate \Nsomeone else's research,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.65,0:05:34.38,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,you must show results as counter-evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.12,0:05:38.02,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If you're an alchemist, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.58,0:05:42.60,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Without substantiation, the professor \Nwould never change his thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:44.30,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.82,0:05:49.10,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I will devote all of myself \Nto trying to persuade you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:51.95,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Observe with your own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.39,0:05:54.37,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Something which you have created...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.37,0:05:56.77,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,is exhibiting a value \Nwhich you did not know of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.77,0:05:58.07,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Just look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.90,0:06:08.78,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I understand flame reactions and the \Neffect of black powder, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:12.26,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I never imagined a use like this existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.43,0:06:46.83,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You're amazing, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:49.90,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,No, you're the amazing one, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.77,0:06:55.23,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm sure that there are other things \Nwhich you thought could only be poisons
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.23,0:06:57.72,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,which have other splendid uses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.33,0:07:03.88,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,After all, you're the most \Nbrilliant alchemist in all the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.72,0:07:12.21,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.97,0:07:19.24,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,So, I was able to create the source \Nof something that beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.72,0:07:28.82,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It seems they all launched safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.49,0:07:37.18,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:39.58,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,It was really a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.78,0:07:43.35,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Could you give this to everyone for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:46.02,flashback,Theodore,0,0,0,,This? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.48,0:07:48.90,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The amount of black powder\N and where it was set...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.90,0:07:52.25,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Because I saw his experiment \Nplanner in my third life,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.25,0:07:55.26,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I could narrow down the possibilities, \Neven in this large capital city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.24,0:07:58.58,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,After that, I took the \Nprofessor's area of activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:08:01.80,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and looked for spots that \Nmatched the right conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.74,0:08:08.87,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The rest was all thanks to everyone involved \Nin this matter doing their jobs perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.48,0:08:13.90,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness's retainers really \Nare exceptional, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:20.01,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Lord Lawvine?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.99,0:08:22.62,Default,Lawvine's knight 2,0,0,0,,As you ordered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.62,0:08:23.59,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.14,0:08:25.44,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Michel Hévin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:28.32,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,This incident. You will \Nhave to explain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:30.16,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Wait, Lawvine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.16,0:08:32.57,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I will take charge of that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.57,0:08:33.87,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I cannot allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.87,0:08:34.82,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:38.02,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,This individual declared that he \Nwould cause an incident here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.02,0:08:40.73,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,on land governed by His Majesty, the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:43.94,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Even though the order comes from \Nyou, Prince Theodore,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.94,0:08:46.46,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I cannot hand him over to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.25,0:08:56.63,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is this commotion, Lawvine?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.55,0:09:00.04,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.26,0:09:04.64,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I received a report of an individual \Nmaking nefarious declarations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.64,0:09:08.90,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Believing him to be connected to the \Nlarge flames seen in the air just now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:11.80,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,I've captured him and \Nintend to interrogate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.24,0:09:13.78,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.78,0:09:15.54,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, earlier, those—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.54,0:09:16.39,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.91,0:09:18.28,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,That is unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.59,0:09:23.04,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,That phenomenon just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.04,0:09:27.17,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,it was no more than a scholar of Coyolles \Ndemonstrating a new technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.21,0:09:34.84,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Why would a Coyolles scholar unveil a \Nnew technology here, in our country?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.28,0:09:43.47,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Our empire will be forming a technological \Npartnership with Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:02.19,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,In exchange for providing military \Ninstruction to Coyolles,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.19,0:10:06.83,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,we will be borrowing their precision \Nmachining techniques and academic knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.83,0:10:08.80,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Those flowers of flame we saw earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.80,0:10:13.25,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,served as proof that Coyolles possesses \Ntechnologies unknown to our empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.13,0:10:15.46,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:19.76,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.35,0:10:21.18,Default,Lawvine,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.12,0:10:23.47,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Lord Lawvine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.14,0:10:28.14,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I apologize for hiding my \Nidentity all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.20,0:10:35.28,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Michel!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.28,0:10:39.45,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I'm happy for your help forming this \Nalliance, but that took me completely by surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.45,0:10:40.34,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.95,0:10:43.88,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,If you wanted to unveil the \Nresults of your research,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.88,0:10:47.20,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,there must have been methods which would \Nhave caused less trouble for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.20,0:10:48.31,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You have it wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:50.79,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,The truth is that lives would have—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.79,0:10:52.15,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor Michel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.58,0:10:55.71,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Right now, please just stay quiet \Nand let him be angry with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.43,0:11:02.47,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.47,0:11:04.28,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.77,0:11:05.58,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Michel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.31,0:11:07.72,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I won't do it any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.40,0:11:11.52,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,My theory was hugely flawed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.52,0:11:12.90,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I understand that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.62,0:11:18.40,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I promise you that I will never do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.15,0:11:23.64,Default,Oliver,0,0,0,,Then, I shall make the proper arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.48,0:11:33.92,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I will say this: I am not acting \Nout of kindness towards them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.32,0:11:37.92,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's abundantly clear that he \Nwas plotting something unsavory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:41.36,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,However, if he were publicly \Ntreated as a criminal,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.36,0:11:43.38,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,my father, the emperor, would hear of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.38,0:11:45.95,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,That's why I made use of your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.95,0:11:48.46,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.94,0:11:52.50,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,After I explain the details \Nregarding the professor,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.50,0:11:54.38,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I look forward to your \Njudgment on the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.13,0:11:56.69,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,How commendable of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.69,0:11:59.64,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If I choose to kill and \Ndispose of him in secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.64,0:12:02.20,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I will hear no complaints from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.62,0:12:08.20,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.05,0:12:11.20,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.13,0:12:17.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The truth is, the person who invented \Nthe pocket watch was Professor Michel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.86,0:12:23.61,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If we will be conducting joint \Nresearch with Coyolles,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.61,0:12:27.35,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,won't Professor Michel's knowledge be needed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.35,0:12:30.83,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.35,0:12:32.72,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.11,0:12:37.31,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,No matter how I look at \Nthis, you were confident
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.31,0:12:39.73,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,you could convince me \Nfrom the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.73,0:12:41.12,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,How could I be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.12,0:12:44.08,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The only thing I was confident of was that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.08,0:12:47.55,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness would be \Ninterested in the professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.74,0:12:53.87,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The people in town will \Nhave seen those fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:56.13,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,When people learn that \Nthey were from Coyolles,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:12:58.62,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I think they will support the alliance, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.43,0:13:01.07,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,They probably will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.07,0:13:01.93,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.75,0:13:06.44,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,So, those are called fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.44,0:13:09.05,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, that's what I've named them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.57,0:13:15.16,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I wanted you to see those \Nfireworks, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.25,0:13:22.03,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The black powder used in fireworks \Nis a dangerous substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.03,0:13:24.79,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,However, depending upon how it's used,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.79,0:13:28.67,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,it can also create a beautiful sight the \Nlikes of which no one has seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:35.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you learned that, then you would \Ncarve a path to many more possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.60,0:13:37.58,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's my thinking on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.66,0:13:46.78,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Right now, he may still believe that \Nall of his abilities are meant for war,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.68,0:13:50.49,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,but one day, I'm certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:14:00.65,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,This medicine will help with\N seasickness on your journey home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.65,0:14:03.10,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The flavor is as awful as ever, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.10,0:14:06.78,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Compared to the suffering of \Nseasickness, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.23,0:14:09.29,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:12.23,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Truly, thank you so very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.68,0:14:15.20,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,It's only because you lent us your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:18.67,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,that Prince Arnold formed an \Nalliance with our kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.67,0:14:24.17,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,No, it was Coyolles' sound technological \Nprowess and support of academic research.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.17,0:14:27.92,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,This is all the result of you doing \Neverything in your power, Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.58,0:14:36.68,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I think that your husband \Nis far too magnanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.29,0:14:38.94,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Not at all, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:41.16,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,He's telling you that in this joint venture,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.16,0:14:44.69,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,you should continue producing \Nthe very best of results.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:48.76,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's a severe punishment which the average \Nperson wouldn't be able to shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.76,0:14:51.77,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Yes, I suppose it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.26,0:14:56.38,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,"Create things which will make \Nthe world more wonderful."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.38,0:14:59.98,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I've never done any research \Nin that area before...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.80,0:15:02.97,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,but I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.00,0:15:09.90,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I wanted to apologize to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:15.75,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I was mistaken when I said that you \Nweren't suited to being an empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:18.26,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You're more than suited to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.87,0:15:23.07,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,But it's true that I see it as a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.66,0:15:26.35,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You won't regret it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.35,0:15:29.61,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,A life as the bride of Arnold Hein.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.00,0:15:35.67,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Right now, what I most want to know about \Nis the man who will become my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.67,0:15:39.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I want to know him more than I want \Nto know any research result or theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:43.38,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,And so we part for a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.53,0:15:47.96,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Let's meet again, my student.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:51.34,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.23,0:16:00.10,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor Michel was taken aback.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.10,0:16:02.56,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,He said Prince Arnold is "too magnanimous."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.41,0:16:08.38,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rather than making a fuss over \Nsomething which ended in failure,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.38,0:16:11.86,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,making good use of him makes \Nmore sense. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:13.93,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.42,0:16:25.50,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I have one more thing to report.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:32.04,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.04,0:16:32.95,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.76,0:16:36.70,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I wanted to see the finished \Npiece with you, Your Highness,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:38.46,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,so I haven't opened it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.96,0:16:40.39,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.51,0:16:40.39,top,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.06,0:16:44.77,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Showing me that you're wearing \Nthat ring is unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:52.78,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,By unnecessary, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.78,0:16:54.32,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.32,0:16:59.56,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,The only thing that I requested of you \Nwas to allow me to gift you a ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.48,0:17:07.29,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I have no right to wish \Nfor any more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.29,0:17:11.69,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You may have allowed me to gift you with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.69,0:17:14.80,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,but you needn't wear something \Nwhich doesn't meet your standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.28,0:17:18.40,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You should wear only that which you like,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.40,0:17:20.31,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,with no regard for the gazes of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.31,0:17:21.80,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Choose freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.52,0:17:28.31,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.00,0:17:30.07,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.50,0:17:32.40,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,When they were measuring my size,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.40,0:17:35.40,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I chose the third finger \Non my left hand, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.91,0:17:36.96,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.96,0:17:42.98,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,In my country, when people are married, the \Nhusband places a ring on the wife's third finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:50.59,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I long to experience that sort of ritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.46,0:17:56.07,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I want to wear this ring \Nfor the marriage ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.07,0:17:58.22,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,and I will chose my dress to match it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.22,0:18:00.32,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You say that it's unnecessary,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:03.10,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,but I'm going to wear this ring everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:03.72,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:08.23,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If anything, I've been restraining \Nmyself from putting it on immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.22,0:18:13.32,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,So, Prince Arnold, please \Nput it on my finger for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.32,0:18:15.66,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I'm not wearing gloves right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.99,0:18:22.03,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's all right, even without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.20,0:18:29.18,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I just really want it to happen right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.71,0:18:30.66,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.23,0:18:34.07,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.39,0:19:13.38,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.99,0:19:20.34,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,May I touch you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.39,0:19:27.27,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.74,0:19:35.96,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Hey, don't hold your breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.96,0:19:37.73,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm not holding my breath!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.50,0:19:41.40,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I've simply forgotten how \Nto breathe, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.78,0:19:43.98,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He laughed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.56,0:20:06.83,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Have you remembered how to breathe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.83,0:20:08.42,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.28,0:20:19.28,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.02,0:20:24.06,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:39.44,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It really is exactly the same \Ncolor as Your Highness's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:45.01,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Just wearing this ring makes me feel \Nlike I can accomplish anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.76,0:20:50.70,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.44,0:20:52.17,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:02.57,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It puts me in an even better \Nmood than I'd imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.76,0:21:08.93,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.93,0:21:09.78,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.49,0:21:13.99,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The number of things I want \Nto ask of you has increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.99,0:21:17.46,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Tell me. Right now, I'd grant you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.89,0:21:22.38,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I want to go on a journey \Nwith you, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.38,0:21:23.39,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,A journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.39,0:21:28.34,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes. A journey to see all of the \Nbeautiful things in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.34,0:21:30.76,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Not just fireflies and fireworks...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:37.44,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I want to go and find many more things \Nthat you think are lovely and beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.50,0:21:41.48,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, I've found \None more of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.48,0:21:42.08,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.55,0:21:44.11,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.53,0:21:46.51,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What indeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.99,0:21:50.69,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you don't know, then I won't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.69,0:21:52.16,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Th-That isn't fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:55.08,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Do you really think an average person \Ncan measure up to one of your riddles?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.08,0:21:57.73,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,An average person would not explode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.73,0:22:00.90,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,a mysterious compound in the sky \Nover their betrothed's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.57,0:22:14.14,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Though, I don't think this riddle \Nis so very difficult to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:24.77,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Right now, they may only be \Nthe slightest of changes...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.68,0:22:30.47,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,but as one piles on another, little by \Nlittle the future should change, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.60,0:22:36.50,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I hope to see a beautiful future \Ntogether with Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.97,0:22:44.03,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In this life, that is the great \Nobjective I have found for myself.
